The Sunken Sanctum was the hidden proving-ground of the Spirebound Conclave in the Cinderteeth Range.
Founding doctrine of Continuance: no discovery, oath, or lesson should die with its keeper.

Three factions: Ember Canon (will through fire), Prism Thesis (memory through crystal), Pale Ledger (testimony through spirit imprinting).

When border wars severed supply routes, Continuance shifted from scholarly ideal to survival engine.
Volunteers were replaced by condemned debtors under sealed warrants from lowland magistrates.
Record language changed: "binding" for coercion, "elevation" for vivisection, "custody" for imprisonment.

Experiments produced: Flamebound Sentinels (fire-etched veterans), Shadow Stalkers (unleashable scout prototypes), Spirit Mages (mnemonic echoes chained to incomplete duties).

Collapse: an authorized change order countersigned by rival offices introduced contradictory lock states during a seismic event.
Upper armouries ignited. Crystal conduits fractured. Undercroft pumps reversed, drawing glacial melt into ritual basements.

Regional powers declared the mountain cursed and collapsed the upper approaches.
The sanctum was entombed by policy. No recovery team arrived.
Surviving systems still pulse in the dark, preserving horrors the Conclave started and never finished.
